"```sql\nSELECT SUM(posts.CommentCount)\nFROM posts\nJOIN users ON posts.OwnerUserId = users.Id\nWHERE users.DisplayName = 'csgillespie';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the total number of comments for all posts owned by the user with the display name \"csgillespie\". It does this by joining the `posts` table with the `users` table using the `OwnerUserId` foreign key, and then summing the `CommentCount` for posts where the `DisplayName` matches \"csgillespie\"."